<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-14T06:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-14T06:25:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1806: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-14T14:00:00+02:35">October 14, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received October 14—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>129. My 125, October 12, noon. In view of Italian Minister’s
                                    condition the Emperor has decided to permit him to remain until
                                    the expected consular agent arrives which should be in a few
                                    days. Vinci and his Military Attaché occupy a house which was
                                    put at their disposal on October 12th.</p>
                                <p>I cannot speak too highly of the police protection afforded him
                                    throughout this deplorable incident and the consideration and
                                    dignity with which he has been treated by the authorities.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>